This repository contains the text of a theoretical law that could be implemented by any structure of state in the future to accomodate a long term energy crisis due to the shortage of fuels. At the time of this writing
the possible crisis could be peak oil production.

These policies are neutral about the value of labor, regulating costs and sizes of physical objects, most likely resulting in inflated prices.

The first principle is the reduction of the gross vehicle weight, the size of the largest transportation trucks, and thus the size of all other items in the economy of a society.
